Veterinary Knowledge Suite — Deploy notes

This repository contains a Dockerfile and a GitHub Actions workflow to deploy the Shiny app to Fly.io.

Quick steps to enable automated deploys from GitHub:

1) Create a Fly API token locally:
   - Install flyctl: https://fly.io/docs/hands-on/install-flyctl/
   - Run: flyctl auth login
   - Then: flyctl auth token
   Copy the printed token.

2) Add the token to this repository secrets:
   - GitHub → Settings → Secrets → Actions → New repository secret
   - Name: FLY_API_TOKEN
   - Value: <paste the token from flyctl auth token>

3) Push to main (the workflow triggers on push to main). The workflow uses remote build on Fly and will deploy the app named "vademecumapp" in region "ams".

4) Check deploy logs:
   - In GitHub Actions: the workflow run shows the deploy steps.
   - On Fly: flyctl logs (requires flyctl and auth on your machine).

Notes:
- The app reads info.xlsx from the repository root. To update data you can either update the Excel file and push a new commit, or change the app to read from an external data source (Sheets, DB, S3).
- If the Docker build fails due to missing system libraries, add the required apt packages to the Dockerfile.
